  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat, then once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676375755046-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676375755046-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676375755046-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676375755046-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676375755046-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once starting to soften, add your <strong>diced chicken breast </strong>and cook for 10-12 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) and the onion is caramelised</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat set aside – this is your <strong>cooked chicken breast </strong>and<strong> caramelised onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676375766911-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676375766911-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676375766911-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676375766911-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676375766911-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> farfalle</strong> to a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>,<strong> </strong>bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will go in the oven later!</p><p>Once cooked, drain the farfalle, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong> and reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
